Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.83,0:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.85,0:00:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are waiting for the moment{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.53,0:00:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The words we exchange{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and a chance meeting{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}People, no matter who they are,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}As we leave behind a\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}living testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}the Galaxy Railways on which{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.86,0:01:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Currently, there is a planet{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}about to quietly pass away.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.86,0:01:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}This mothering planet,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}which has nurtured so many lives,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.16,0:01:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and is now becoming{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}aware of its own death,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.20,0:02:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}is unable to escape the fate{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}that now threatens it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.14,0:02:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Twilight"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.82,0:02:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The next train will be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Galaxy Railways No. 330,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.25,0:02:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}leaving from Platform 3 at 3:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.82,0:02:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Those boarding, please proceed slowly,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}without pushing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.16,0:02:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There are still other trains\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that will be departing later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.40,0:02:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please do not force\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your way onto any trains.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.83,0:02:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you could show\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your emigration permits,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.37,0:02:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}you will be able to transfer to a train\N{\c&He1e1e1&}bound for your destination world
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.47,0:02:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}at no charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.17,0:02:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}so please do not worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.52,0:02:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Transfer of all residents from District A\N{\c&He1e1e1&}through District F is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.19,0:02:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I have my people heading out to confirm\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that there are no more residents
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.49,0:02:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}still around in any of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the outlying districts now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.53,0:02:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once that is done, the transfer of all\N{\c&He1e1e1&}residents will be successfully completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.86,0:03:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you for your efforts. It is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}an honor to have the SDF assisting us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.80,0:03:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, the population transfer\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from Planet Arbent here
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.41,0:03:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}is a matter of highest priority\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to Galaxy Railways Headquarters,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.14,0:03:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and it is the SDF's duty to ensure\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the safety of the population,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.18,0:03:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}who will be our passengers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.82,0:03:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Today, the day has arrived\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when this station will be closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.82,0:03:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We appreciate all your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.83,0:03:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.16,0:03:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is a heartless affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.17,0:03:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}To think that in one year,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.80,0:03:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}everything will be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}swallowed up by the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.84,0:03:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This planet is like one\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of your children, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.57,0:03:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So this planet is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}about to disappear, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.81,0:03:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's something\N{\c&He1e1e1&}so depressing about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.91,0:03:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Louis. There's nobody left\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in District F. How about District G?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.58,0:04:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There isn't a single person here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.52,0:04:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's so lonesome. What about you, Manabu?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.52,0:04:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's the same here in District H.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.52,0:04:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm heading to District I next.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.86,0:04:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay, we'll leave that to you, {\i1}Yuuki-kun.{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I doubt anyone will be there, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.20,0:04:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right, let's bet on it!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}10,000 ables says there's nobody there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.87,0:04:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nobody's going to take you up on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.57,0:04:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This can't be right, can it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's the real thing. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.85,0:05:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...all the agricultural land\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has been abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.79,0:05:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There shouldn't be anyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.19,0:05:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey! What are you doing to my fields!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.86,0:05:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How can you toy around with something
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.67,0:05:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}that somebody sweat over\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to raise so carefully!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.20,0:05:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you going to apologize, or not!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.20,0:05:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}S- sorry. I didn't think\N{\c&He1e1e1&}anyone was here, so I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.21,0:05:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.55,0:05:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've finally come home, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.55,0:05:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Makoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.56,0:05:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your mother has been waiting all this\N{\c&He1e1e1&}time for you to come home! Makoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.56,0:05:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Uh, I'm not Makoto, I'm Manabu.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Er, did you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.90,0:05:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Makoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You came home right out of the blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.01,0:06:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and I was so surprised,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}my heart nearly stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.51,0:06:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Kusanagi Ine"\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Really, you're such an ungrateful son!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.34,0:06:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Really, you're such an ungrateful son!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.85,0:06:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}B- but, I'm not your child!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.85,0:06:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're not a child anymore? Don't go\N{\c&He1e1e1&}talking to me like you're all grown-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.19,0:06:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No matter how huge a farm\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you might have acquired,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.09,0:06:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}you'll still always be just\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a little child to your mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.86,0:06:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Farm? I told you, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.53,0:06:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's okay, it's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.20,0:06:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You must be worn out from your\N{\c&He1e1e1&}long trip. Here, bottoms up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bottoms up? I'm telling you,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.74,0:06:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm in the middle of checking to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make sure there's nobody left here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.21,0:06:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hmm? How is your work coming along?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.88,0:06:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}F- fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.55,0:06:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I see, I see. Planet reclamation\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is such a tough job.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.99,0:06:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I was worried about\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what would become of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.89,0:06:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Planet reclamation?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, you've realized your\N{\c&He1e1e1&}dream of owning a farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.96,0:07:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Now all you need is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to find yourself a wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.23,0:07:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Or have you already found someone nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.17,0:07:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't have anyone in particular yet...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I mean, I'm not this Makoto person...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.17,0:07:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Goodness gracious!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you being so shy for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.84,0:07:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh my, I haven't put out any tea.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Wait here, I'll go put some on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.18,0:07:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I give up. She's got me\N{\c&He1e1e1&}completely mistaken for her son.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.53,0:07:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Maybe we do look alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.55,0:07:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}She's been waiting a long time{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}for her son to come home to her.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.89,0:08:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}But I can't just leave her{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}here like this.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.99,0:08:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I should contact the captain right away.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.16,0:08:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Makoto...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.50,0:08:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The time is just about right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I- {\i1}Ine-san?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.18,0:08:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is positively weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How could there still be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a field here like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.85,0:08:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I wonder where {\i1}Yuuki-kun{\i0} could have gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.19,0:08:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is he up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.19,0:08:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}P- please, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.86,0:08:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.86,0:08:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.03,0:08:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.87,0:08:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun,{\i0} are you okay!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.87,0:08:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just a minute, I tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.87,0:08:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's nothing to be bashful about!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}How can you take a bath with these on?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.54,0:08:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right! I'll take them off myself,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}just let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.88,0:09:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you trying to do with\N{\c&He1e1e1&}this old lady while you're on duty?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.15,0:09:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ah, I'm saved! You two,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}explain what's going on to {\i1}Ine-san{\i0} here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.16,0:09:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Explain?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.16,0:09:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, this girl must be your wife-to-be.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}She's cute, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.16,0:09:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And she has one of your hired hands\N{\c&He1e1e1&}with her. I could tell in once glance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.83,0:09:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What does she mean,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}wife-to-be, {\i1}Yuuki-kun!?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.50,0:09:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hold on now,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what do you mean, hired hand!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.17,0:09:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, you see... it's like...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.51,0:09:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've left yourself open!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, she thinks that Yuuki is her son?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.85,0:09:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes. She has him\N{\c&He1e1e1&}completely mistaken for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.52,0:09:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and won't listen to a word we say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.52,0:09:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It appears that Old Lady Ine\N{\c&He1e1e1&}thinks her son Makoto
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.29,0:09:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}has come home after\N{\c&He1e1e1&}successfully developing Planet Agri,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.19,0:09:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and he's brought his girlfriend\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and hired hand along with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.53,0:09:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why should I have to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.53,0:09:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, you're the hired hand, huh?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}That's some fine casting there!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.87,0:09:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.87,0:10:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I understand the situation.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}But our time is limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.74,0:10:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Carry out your duties with all haste.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.21,0:10:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger. I'll tell Manabu as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.55,0:10:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}A wheat field... District I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.22,0:10:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Carry out... with all haste..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.22,0:10:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's what he said.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}So if you don't mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.90,0:10:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What a tone to take with your boss!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}You'll never be promoted like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.24,0:10:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How terribly rude of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.24,0:10:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You should fire that ill-mannered\N{\c&He1e1e1&}hired hand of yours at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.81,0:10:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're so kind-hearted,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I worry about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.58,0:10:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's all right. Despite it all,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}he's still very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}More importantly, I have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}something imperative to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.35,0:10:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This planet is about to...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.59,0:10:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You sure have grown.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.25,0:10:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That little boy grew up to be so big.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.19,0:10:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You were a crybaby,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}but you would never give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.26,0:10:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And you would always go over\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and apologize with me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.50,0:10:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}whenever you got into an fight\N{\c&He1e1e1&}with someone. Do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.22,0:11:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You don't say. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.89,0:11:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You don't have to apologize now.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}My boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.56,0:11:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}taking off from here, saying you're\N{\c&He1e1e1&}going to develop some new land,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.33,0:11:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}like your late father did
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.23,0:11:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}coming home such a strapping young man...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm glad I waited for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.91,0:11:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're going to stay with me forever,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}right Makoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.93,0:12:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I'm glad I waited for you. You're going{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to stay with me forever, right Makoto?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.87,0:12:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}No, I'm not. I'm going to...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.88,0:12:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I'm just going to have{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to tell her the truth.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.88,0:12:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}That I'm not Makoto-san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}That I'm not really her son.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.56,0:12:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Ine-san,{\i0} I want you to listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.22,0:12:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Y- yes, there, there.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Ah, there's a butler for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.16,0:12:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You know where all the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}right pressure points are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.23,0:12:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why, thank you... Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.57,0:12:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry to trouble you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to help out, too, Driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.57,0:12:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not at all. I'm used to physical labor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.57,0:12:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't be concerned.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}This is right up his alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.24,0:12:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Isn't that right, Driver?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.58,0:12:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.58,0:12:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's this? I put out a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}change of clothes for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.92,0:12:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}yet you put on that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}dirty outfit again? My word...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.26,0:13:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And another thing, you should have told\N{\c&He1e1e1&}me from the start that you were inviting
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.69,0:13:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}your butler and driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.19,0:13:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I have things that I need\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to get ready, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.86,0:13:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please, do not concern yourself over us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.87,0:13:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You too, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.20,0:13:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I wonder how many decades it has been\N{\c&He1e1e1&}since I've had so many visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.21,0:13:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll have to knock myself out tonight\N{\c&He1e1e1&}preparing something good for you to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.88,0:13:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Louis-san?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.88,0:13:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.88,0:13:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Give me a hand, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.88,0:13:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I would be only too happy to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.22,0:13:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Um... There's a good reason\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.89,0:13:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.89,0:13:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.56,0:13:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's my fault. She kept going at it\N{\c&He1e1e1&}faster than I could keep up with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.24,0:13:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But Old Lady Ine is just waiting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for her son to come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.21,0:13:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If we could persuade\N{\c&He1e1e1&}her real son to come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.58,0:13:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I think he would understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.24,0:14:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, isn't there anything we can\N{\c&He1e1e1&}do to track down her son? If we can...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.52,0:14:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That won't be possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.52,0:14:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I realize that it's a departure\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from our regular SDF duties, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.19,0:14:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...at this rate, even if we were\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to take her with us against her will...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.52,0:14:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Her son is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.86,0:14:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There, see? That's how you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.20,0:14:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't be so impressed by this. You won't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}be fit to be Makoto's wife like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.21,0:14:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}B- but I told you,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not his wife-to-be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, dear, I don't have any tomatoes,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}which he likes so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll go pick some\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from the field out back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.22,0:14:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Destroyed? Planet Agri?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.22,0:14:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But they're supposed to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}conduct a careful investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.26,0:14:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}of planets to be developed beforehand,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.56,0:14:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Repeated terraforming must have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}shortened the life of the planet itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.90,0:14:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ten years ago, the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}planetary crust collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.91,0:15:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There was never a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}single confirmed survivor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.85,0:15:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Then, no matter how long\N{\c&He1e1e1&}she waits for {\i1}Makoto-san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.18,0:15:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...he's no longer of this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.19,0:15:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What do you plan to do, Yuuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.52,0:15:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.53,0:15:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you two discussing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}something to do with work?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.86,0:15:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, just chit-chatting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.20,0:15:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Then, would you mind if I borrow\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Makoto away for a bit to go somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.54,0:15:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where is it we're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.87,0:15:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Isn't it obvious? Your favorite place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.22,0:15:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why can't I cut this!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.56,0:15:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.42,0:15:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Did you take care of these wheat fields\N{\c&He1e1e1&}by yourself all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.43,0:16:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes, indeed I did, so that you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}could come home at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.10,0:16:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You would be disappointed if the landscape\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of your home were to disappear, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.43,0:16:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}This whole planet is going{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to disappear before long.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.77,0:16:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}In another year or so... it's going{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to be swallowed up by that sun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.12,0:16:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We have to get away\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from this place, soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.89,0:16:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Galaxy Railways can\N{\c&He1e1e1&}take you anywhere. So please...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.46,0:16:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't leave this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.13,0:16:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is precious land,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.13,0:16:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}which has been handed down\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from generation to generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.47,0:16:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I simply cannot leave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.47,0:16:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.14,0:16:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Besides, this is your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.15,0:16:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You really have been kindhearted,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}ever since you were a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.75,0:16:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay, let's keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.09,0:17:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.09,0:17:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.77,0:17:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's so pretty...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.78,0:17:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This view is going to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}disappear before long.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.11,0:17:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.13,0:17:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Am I too heavy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.13,0:17:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.13,0:17:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You really have grown up strong, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're taking more and more\N{\c&He1e1e1&}after your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.47,0:17:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nothing could make me happier\N{\c&He1e1e1&}than being carried by my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.81,0:17:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The truth is, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.74,0:17:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...I'm really not...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.08,0:18:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...I'm really not {\i1}Makoto-san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.08,0:18:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Which is why...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.76,0:18:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.76,0:18:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Here! Look over there, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.11,0:18:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You enjoyed the view from here.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}You would say, "This is my home."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.78,0:18:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Home...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.78,0:18:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's more...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.78,0:18:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...we managed to get\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a good crop this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.25,0:18:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The flavor hasn't changed\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.46,0:18:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And neither has the view.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}But it's all going to disappear, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.80,0:18:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You won't ever be able\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to see it again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.47,0:18:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just like my boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.07,0:18:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.74,0:19:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Ine-san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.41,0:19:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Delicious!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.08,0:19:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please let me have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.42,0:19:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It would be a shame to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}lose fruit this delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.76,0:19:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll plant it on a new planet.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll grow more of them, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.43,0:19:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}How many nights have I\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}spent alone since then?{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll plant it on a new planet.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll grow more of them, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}How many nights have I\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}spent alone since then?{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}First on Planet Agri,
